values: I want something or someone to do again. I'm so bored, it's beyond even comprehensible. And Flint, if you make one comment about jumping off a bridge again, I swear to Merlin I will hurt you. Or someone will do it for me.

I'm bored, and looking for something to do. Basically, that's it, that's all. I am bored out of my mind - even school was more enjoyable than this! Honestly. Someone - anyone - suggest something that I could do. Please.

Draco's daughter really is sweet. Evita...she's a bit spoiled, but that's to be expected, I'm supposing. She's also rather ticklish. Takes after her father, that one. Tracey? Morag? We have to get together at one point. Really, catching up is a must.

So, it looks like Draco's little girl, Evita, is coming for a week. As much as I loathe admitting it, I love when she comes. She's such a sweet little child, and she looks so adorable. How he plans on running a casino while she's here, I don't know. But that's his problem, not mine.

They changed the light filters in the club again, and now they're blue. I wish they would just leave them -- for at least a week! Just a few days ago they were gold. And now I have to redo my entire makeup plans and costumes for the entire week. And people say that being a showgirl is an easy job. That's definitely not true. And Draco? Are you..stopping by this evening before the show?
